value.value: A fiducial marker consisting of implanted gold seeds.
An implanted stent that is used as a surrogate fiducial marker.
A manufactured object that is used to perform diagnostic, therapeutic or research activities.
An implanted surgical clip that is used as a surrogate fiducial marker.
The name of the radiation therapy prescription used to distinguish it from other prescriptions.

An image registration process that can correct for changes in compared images by mapping between volume elements in one image and the corresponding volume elements in a subsequent image. Unlike rigid image registration, deformable image registration can account for non-linear displacements.

A simple image registration process that uses a linear transformation model to overlay two or more images from various scanners taken at different times and angles. This method may not account for changes in the weight of the patient between scans, changes in the positioning of the patient, and soft-tissue displacements due to breathing.
A posterior recumbent body position whereby the person lies on their back and faces upward with the lower extremities moderately flexed and rotated outward.

label.value: Duration of Radiation Delivery in Session

value.value: The length of time during a treatment session that the patient was irradiated. A session is defined as the period of time between when the patient enters the treatment room and when they leave it.

label.value: Duration of Treating Field Radiation in Fraction

value.value: The time in seconds from start to end of delivery of therapeutic radiation associated with the field.

label.value: Duration of Treating Plan Radiation in Fraction

value.value: The time in seconds from the first delivery of therapeutic radiation in the session to the last delivery of therapeutic radiation in the session to treat the plan.
The length of time a treatment session lasts. A session is defined as the period of time between when the patient enters the treatment room and when they leave it.
A modulation method used during treatment to compensate for intrafraction motion.
infant death due to AIDS
The method used in the treatment plan to manipulate the beam to cover the area irradiated.
The manner in which image sets for the component plans were registered when the treatment plan is the sum of multiple plans.

label.value: Date of Report of Androgen Deprivation Therapy

value.value: The date on which the androgen deprivation therapy was initiated.
The date on which the charge was reported.

label.value: Date of Report of Function Test Result

value.value: The date on which the function test result was reported.
The date on which the immunotherapy was initiated.
A class of compounds isolated from a marine cyanobacterium species (blue green alga).  Curacin compounds inhibit tubulin polymerization, thereby inhibiting mitosis and cell proliferation. (NCI)
Mutagenesis where the mutation is caused by the loss of DNA sequences within a gene. This may occur spontaneously in vivo or be experimentally induced in vivo or in vitro.

label.value: Date of Report of Interventional Procedure

value.value: The date on which the interventional procedure was reported.

label.value: Date of Report of Patient Encounter

value.value: The date on which the patient encounter was reported.

value.value: The date on which the patient reported outcome was recorded.

label.value: Date of Report of Patient Treatment Outcome

value.value: The date on which the patient treatment outcome was reported.

value.value: The date on which the performance score was reported.

value.value: The date on which the provider reported toxicity was recorded.

label.value: Date of Report of Radiation Therapy Course

value.value: The date on which the radiation therapy course was reported.

label.value: Date of Report of Radiation Therapy Course Event

value.value: The date on which the radiation therapy course event was reported.

label.value: Date of Report of Radiation Therapy Course Session

value.value: The date on which the radiation therapy course session was reported.

label.value: Date of Report of Radiation Therapy Prescription

value.value: The date on which the radiation therapy prescription was reported.

Molecular biology procedure used to determine the 5' end or 3' end of a nucleic acid molecule, or the location of the junction between spliced molecules.  Used most commonly to determine the 5' end of RNA transcripts.  Based on the protection afforded an end-labeled DNA probe from nuclease S1 digestion after hybridization with a target molecule.  The length of the protected probe indicates the end or molecular junction of the target nucleic acid sequence.

label.value: Date of Report of Reirradiation Evaluation

value.value: The date on which the reirradiation evaluation was reported.

value.value: The date on which the supportive medication was reported.

value.value: The date on which the systemic therapy course was reported.

value.value: The date on which the systemic therapy cycle was reported.

label.value: Date of Report of Treated Field in Treated Radiation Therapy Plan Fraction

value.value: The date on which the treated field in treated radiation therapy plan fraction was reported.

label.value: Date of Report of Treated Radiation Therapy Plan

value.value: The date on which the treated radiation therapy plan was reported.

The dose obtained using a 2 gray fraction dose, which is biologically equivalent to the total dose (D) given with a fraction dose (d) of gray. The values of equivalent dose in 2 gray fractions (EQD2) may be added in separate parts in the treatment plan.
Proton beam radiation therapy in which the proton beam is applied constantly.

label.value: Uniform Active Scanning Proton Beam Therapy

value.value: A hybrid of active scanning and passively scattered proton therapy.
Fractionated radiation therapy where the fraction size ranges from 240-340 cGy as compared to the 180-200 cGy fraction size used in conventional fractionation.
The NEO Gene confers resistance to the aminoglycoside antibiotic neomycin. NEO is widely used in genetic research because of the easily selectable phenotype.
Fractionated radiation therapy where the fraction size greater than or equal to 500 cGy as compared to the 240-340 cGy fraction size used in moderate hypofractionation.
The spatial orientation of the body during treatment.
A supine position in which hips and knees are flexed and the legs are abducted.

A near sitting position in which the body is lowered while the knees and hips are bent and the weight is supported on one's ankles and feet. The chest is up and the thighs are nearly parallel to the floor.
A recurrence of disease in distant lymph nodes.

label.value: Recurrence of CHAARTED High Volume Metastatic Disease

value.value: A recurrence of high volume metastatic disease as defined by the CHAARTED Study (Chemohormonal Therapy Versus Androgen Ablation Randomized Trial for Extensive Disease in Prostate Cancer) as four or more bone metastases with at least one outside the axial skeleton, or the presence of visceral metastases.
